@HiroPro2 A constant bit rate, though causing the song size to be larger is much better.  I encode music with LAME but with a CBR at 320 kbps.  They sound superb to anything. Also it is recorded at a 45100 Hz frequency which works wonders. :) I do agree with you on Joint-Stereo so the sounds amazing out of 1 or more speakers.  You don't always have to have a "pair" of speakers.

Anyways,  Thanks NoFS, great quality as always so no complaints.  I understand everyones different perspectives on how the want their music.

